by what yardstick do you measure age what do you consider to be middle age what do you consider to be a senior citizen i suspect depending on your current age we'll see varied answers when i was i said to myself hmmm you must be middle aged after all how many people do you know that are i am a sr now and i do have a brain fade now and then but for the most part it is still sharp i am and quit working last fall it was boring for a bit but now i like it go and do as i wish and have lots of fun and laughs with friends if i decide to go and visit friends i don't drive anymore if it is a long distance i ride the bus they even have a tilt cab now so it is easy to get in and out of the bus and the drivers are nice and considerate besides it's sorta fun to watch some of the people on the bus i got a good laugh last fall a totally off the wall lady almost my age she had tats all over and so many piercings in her face and ears she looked like a lightening rod she had on knee high motorcycle boots and jeans and a hemp belt she kept talking about her two daughters meeting her at the bus in wa and said they were going to be amazed over her new piercings after listening to this for an hour i said do you know what i would do if i were your daughters she said no i said i would be standing there and turn to my sis and say look suzie mom didn't get off the bus and walk away drat she missed it Shaggy dog story Social rule Motorcycle Lee Harvey Oswald Avenue Q Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Little Britain American Psycho Drag racing Marilyn Monroe The Lovely Bones Kenny McCormick Rosa Parks 2000 Australian Grand Prix Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban The Adventures of Pete & Pete The Catcher in the Rye Spidey Super Stories Bicycle Comanche Rowan & Martin's Laugh-In Dragon Booster The Amazing Race Sundial Russian joke Milton H. Erickson Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Equine conformation Treehouse of Horror IX Happy Tree Friends The Grim Adventures of Billy a